               <region ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</region>
               <desc facs="Sites/INS0341DL/" n="31">Images</desc>
               
               
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" when="1284">According to the tradition it was founded by 
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName>.</date>

                  <ab type="history">Dabra Libānos, originally known as Dabra ʿAsbo and renamed by
                     
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName> is a monastery located in
                     <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName> in the gorge near the river <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6469ZegaWa">Zega Wädäb</placeName>. This southern location has to be emphasized:
                     the community was established between the kingdom of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2488Damot">Dāmot</placeName> and the Muslim sultanate of
                     <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName> under the authority of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3921Ifat">ʾIfāt</placeName>. According to the
                     hagiography of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1955Anorewos">ʾAnorewos</persName>, one of the first disciples of
                     
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName>, the daily life was
                     under the jurisdiction of the <t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">maggābi</t:roleName>. It is known that the monastery enjoyed land donations at least since the half  of 15th century during
                     the reign of 
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>. The monastery of Dabra Libānos
                     suffered great destruction during the war of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1522Ahmadb">ʾAḥmad</persName> in <date when="1532">1532</date>.
                     However, it revived soon under 
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4428Galawdew">Galāwdewos</persName>
                     and his successor <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8550sardaDe">Śarḍa Dǝngǝl</persName> during which attempts were made to elevate the monastery to
                     the position of religious centre of the monarchy. But the situation deteriorated due to the massive expansion of the
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH1973Oromo">Oromo</persName> and increasing isolation of  Dabra Libānos from the rest of the Empire.
                  </ab>
                  <ab type="description" subtype="school">All levels of the ecclesiastical education are offered, even though some of them are not active. 
                     According to the information obtained in <date notBefore="2020" notAfter="2024">2020-2024</date> by the <ref target="https://www.aai.uni-hamburg.de/en/ethiostudies/research/abennat.html">ʾAbǝnnat project</ref>, the following levels  of traditional education were avaialable: 
                     <table>
                        <row role="label">
                           <cell role="label">School</cell>
                           <cell role="label">Instructor</cell>
                           <cell role="label">Students</cell>
                        </row>                                
                        <row>
                           <cell><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/NebabBet">Nǝbāb bet</ref></cell>
                           <cell>Mamhǝr Walda Iyyāsus, 
                              Mamhǝr Lǝʿul, 
                              Mamhǝr Tasfā,
                              Mamhǝr Walda Madḫǝn
                           </cell>
                           <cell>n.d.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/QeddaseBet">Qǝddāse bet</ref></cell>
                           <cell>Mamhǝr Yamāna Bǝrhān (Retired as of 2024),
                              Mamhǝr Ḥǝzqʾel
                           </cell>
                           <cell>n.d.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ZemaBet#Deggwa">Zemā bet: Dǝggʷā</ref></cell>
                           <cell>Mamhǝr Wadāğ </cell>
                           <cell>n.d.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ZemaBet#Aqwaqwam">Zemā bet: ʾAqqʷāqʷām</ref></cell>
                           <cell>Mamhǝr Batra Māryam (Retired as of 2024),
                              Mamhǝr Sǝmur
                           </cell>
                           <cell>more than 200</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/QeneBet">Qǝne bet</ref></cell>
                           <cell>Mamhǝr Kǝnfa Mikaʾel,
                              Mamhǝr Ḥāwaz
                           </cell>
                           <cell>n.d.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/MashafBet#OldT">Maṣḥāf bet: Old Testament ʾAndǝmtā</ref></cell>
                           <cell>Maggābi bǝluy Bǝrhāna Masqal
                           </cell>
                           <cell>n.d.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/MashafBet#NewT">Maṣḥāf bet: New Testament ʾAndǝmtā</ref></cell>
